text: Please update the "Source Feedback" button/header to use the same element / styles / structure as the "Live Feedback" button/header. Please also add a collapsible header "Description" for the description markdown section that's below Source Feedback.

proposedTasks.title: Unify Source Feedback header to match Live Feedback styling
proposedTasks.description: Update the 'Source Feedback' button/header component in the feedback detail view to use the same element type, CSS classes, and visual structure as the 'Live Feedback' button/header. Both should share a common collapsible-header component (or identical markup pattern) so they look and behave identically. Acceptance criteria: (1) Source Feedback and Live Feedback headers are visually indistinguishable in style, spacing, icon treatment, and collapse/expand behavior; (2) both use the same underlying component or identical markup/class structure; (3) no regressions to existing collapse/expand functionality on Live Feedback.

proposedTasks.title: Add collapsible Description header above description markdown section
proposedTasks.description: Add a new collapsible section header labeled 'Description' that wraps the description markdown content displayed below the Source Feedback section in the feedback detail view. Use the same collapsible-header component/styles established in task 0 for visual consistency. The section should default to expanded. Acceptance criteria: (1) A 'Description' collapsible header appears between Source Feedback and the description markdown content; (2) clicking the header toggles visibility of the description markdown; (3) header styling matches Source Feedback and Live Feedback headers; (4) default state is expanded.

taskTitles: Unify Source Feedback header to match Live Feedback styling
Add collapsible Description header above description markdown section
